    "body": "### Summary\r\n\r\nThe app seems to completely blank the picture's details (description, location, categories) when using the Edit caption feature to edit the caption alone of an uploaded image. An example could be found in the following picture: https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Sunset_view_from_Samanar_hills.jpg\r\n\r\nWhen you look at the history, the edits with \"Updating Description\" completely nuke the media details of the file. If you look closely each such edit is made from the app and is associated with an edit of the caption.\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Open an uploaded image from Contributions screen\r\n2. Tap on the edit description button\r\n3. Change the caption of an image leaving everything else intact\r\n4. Hit \"Submit\"\r\n\r\n### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nOnly the caption should be updated.\r\n\r\n### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nAll media details such as description, location, caption are nuked. \r\n\r\n### Device name\r\n\r\nOnePlus Nord\r\n\r\n### Android version\r\n\r\nAndroid 12\r\n\r\n### Commons app version\r\n\r\nmaster @ 1649d1e2ce1866d14c3225f07e55ff34123cf7d4\r\n\r\n### Device logs\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Screen-shots\r\n\r\n<details><summary>Recording of the issue</summary>\r\n<p>\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/commons-app/apps-android-commons/assets/12448084/64055de2-bf94-422d-a3ef-e83af3765970\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n</details> \r\n\r\n\r\n### Would you like to work on the issue?\r\n\r\nPrefer not",
